FBIS4-6780 "dreas079_c_94009" FBIS-EAS-94-079 Daily Report 23 Apr 1994 North Korea Radio Reports ROK's Hwarang Military Exercise Radio Reports ROK's Hwarang Military Exercise SK2404043794 Pyongyang Korean Central Broadcasting Network in Korean 1200 GMT 23 April 94 SK2404043794 Pyongyang Korean Central Broadcasting Network in Korean 1200 GMT 23 April 94 Korean BFN [Text] According to Seoul radio reports, as soon as warmonger U.S. Defense Secretary Perry left Seoul after hatching a war plot, the Kim Yong-sam traitorous clique announced a plan to stage the Hwarang war exercise in which some 130,000 puppet military personnel, police officers, and reserve forces will be mobilized. The war exercise will take place from 25 April for five consecutive days and will be held in Inchon and areas of Kyonggi Province adjacent to the Military Demarcation Line. In order to instigate hostility and distrust within the nation and heighten antagonism toward the Northern half of the Republic among the South Korean residents, the puppet clique added a drill of countering so-called spy infiltration.
